@startuml
title casbinjs/react - Usage Flow

skinparam shadowing false

actor ReactComponent as Component
participant "Consumer Fetch Layer" as FetchLayer
participant "External Endpoint" as Endpoint
box "casbinjs/react"
participant "CasbinProvider" as Provider
participant "useCasbin()" as UseCasbin
participant "useCan() / useCanAny() / useCanAll()" as UsePermissionHooks
end box
box "casbinjs/core"
participant "Authorizer" as Authorizer
end box

== Initialization ==

FetchLayer -> Endpoint : fetch authorization data
Endpoint --> FetchLayer : policy snapshot
FetchLayer -> Authorizer : createAuthorizer(options)
FetchLayer -> Provider : render with authorizer\nor options
Provider -> Authorizer : provide current authorizer via context

== Hook consumption ==

Component -> UseCasbin : useCasbin()
UseCasbin -> Provider : consume context
Provider --> UseCasbin : authorizer helpers
UseCasbin --> Component : can / canAny / canAll /\naddPolicy / removePolicy / replacePolicies / getEnforcer

Component -> UsePermissionHooks : useCan(...) / useCanAny(...) / useCanAll(...)
UsePermissionHooks -> UseCasbin : use authorizer helpers
UsePermissionHooks --> Component : allowed / isLoading / error

== Permission checks ==

Component -> UsePermissionHooks : useCan(action, resource)
UsePermissionHooks -> Authorizer : can(action, resource)
Authorizer --> UsePermissionHooks : boolean
UsePermissionHooks --> Component : allowed state

== Policy mutation ==

Component -> UseCasbin : addPolicy(policy)
UseCasbin -> Authorizer : addPolicy(policy)
Authorizer --> UseCasbin : completed

Component -> UseCasbin : removePolicy(policy)
UseCasbin -> Authorizer : removePolicy(policy)
Authorizer --> UseCasbin : completed

Component -> UseCasbin : replacePolicies(policies)
UseCasbin -> Authorizer : replacePolicies(policies)
Authorizer --> UseCasbin : completed

note over FetchLayer,Endpoint
Fetching stays app-owned.
tRPC is one possible consumer choice,
not part of the library contract.
end note

note over Provider,UseCasbin
casbinjs/react is the ready-to-use React layer.
end note

note over UsePermissionHooks
Permission hooks wrap async checks into
React-friendly allowed / isLoading / error state.
end note

note over Authorizer
casbinjs/core remains the vanilla-ready interface.
end note
@enduml
